                  <h2>Our Depertment</h2>
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-6">
                      <div class="single_our_depertment">
                        <span class="our_depertment_icon"
                          ><img src="img/icon/feature_2.svg" alt=""
                        /></span>
                        <h4>Intensive Care Unit (ICU)</h4>
                        <p>
                          What is an intensive care unit (ICU)? Intensive care
                          refers to the specialised treatment given to patients
                          who are acutely unwell and require critical medical
                          care.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-6">
                      <div class="single_our_depertment">
                        <span class="our_depertment_icon"
                          ><img src="img/icon/feature_2.svg" alt=""
                        /></span>
                        <h4>Neurology</h4>
                        <p>
                          Neurology deals with the diagnosis and treatment of
                          all categories of conditions and disease involving the
                          central and peripheral nervous systems, including
                          their coverings
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-6">
                      <div class="single_our_depertment">
                        <span class="our_depertment_icon"
                          ><img src="img/icon/feature_2.svg" alt=""
                        /></span>
                        <h4>Cancer Department</h4>
                        <p>
                          The Cancer Department at a hospital is a specialized
                          unit focused on the diagnosis, treatment, and
                          management of cancer. It can also provide support to
                          cancer patients and their families
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-6">
                      <div class="single_our_depertment">
                        <span class="our_depertment_icon"
                          ><img src="img/icon/feature_2.svg" alt=""
                        /></span>
                        <h4>Emergency Department</h4>
                        <p>
                          Emergency department is part of a hospital
                          specifically equipped and staffed to handle critical
                          illnesses and injuries. It operates 24/7 and
                          prioritize patients based on the severity of their
                          condition.
                        </p>
                      </div>
